Williams, AZ Events‎City Council Meeting
August 6, 2018 at 10:49 AM ·

This Thursday (August 9th) our tourism marketing director will be giving her quarterly report at the City Council meeting.

This is her opportunity to communicate her plans and outline what has been accomplished on our behalf in the way of tourism.

You, as a tax payer and resident, might find this interesting!

The Council meeting is Thursday, August 9th at 7pm in the council chambers at City Hall.

Her name is Heather Herman, from Front Burner Media. She gives very interesting reports!

Hope you can make it. Please share!

Kerry-Lynn Moede
The Historic Yellow House

Clean & Beautiful Spring Clean Up Day is APPROACHING!
All week I will "inspire" you with fun anti-littering propaganda.
Aren't you EXCITED?????

Saturday, May 5th 9 am - NOON
Meet at the Visitor Center Parking Lot
Bring gloves, wear a hat and closed-toe shoes.
We provide bags, bag pick up, coffee, cinnamon rolls and lunch.
Find valuable eggs for CASH!
Play the new game sweeping the nation: "You Found WHAT?"

We actually DO have some fun.
Let's make our little town SHINE. (Carol's watching!)
